  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Mounting evidence indicates that the intranasal administration of the neuropeptide oxytocin
      has prosocial effects. However, the neural substrates of these effects are still unclear. The
      investigators hypothesized that a single dose administration of oxytocin should increase
      empathogenic and affiliative responses and that these effects are mediated by an increased
      insula activity.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
